to let you ship your games.  Headings are for clarity only.

1. Grant:  
   Blink Studios (“Licensor”) grants you the rights below so long as you
   follow this License.

2. Internal Use Is Always OK:
   You may use, copy, run, test, and modify the Software inside your own
   organization for any purpose, including commercial work.  These are
   “Permitted Uses”.

3. No Redistribution of the Software:  
   Outside those Permitted Uses you must not distribute, sublicense,
   sell, lease, or otherwise make the Software (in source or object
   form) available to anyone else.

4. Modifications: 
   You may create and use Modifications internally.  All Modifications
   count as part of the Software and inherit this License.

5. Conditions:  
   a. Keep all copyright notices and this License in any source you keep.  
   b. Clearly mark your changes.  
   c. If you somehow distribute the Software in breach of § 3, you’re
      also in breach of this License.

6. Output Exception (Ship Your Games!): 
   You may distribute, sell, or otherwise exploit any *Output* you
   create with the Software — for example, compiled game builds — even
   for profit, **provided** the Software itself (including editor
   scripts and source code) is not exposed or shipped, except as an
   inseparable, compiled‑only component strictly required to run the
   Output.

7. Trademarks:
   This License doesn’t grant you rights to Blink Studios trademarks or
   logos.

8. Disclaimer of Warranty:
   THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED “AS IS”, WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND.

9. Limitation of Liability:  
   LICENSOR IS NEVER LIABLE FOR ANY DIRECT, INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL,
   SPECIAL, EXEMPLARY, OR CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES ARISING FROM THE
   SOFTWARE OR THIS LICENSE.

10. Termination:
    If you break any term of this License, your rights end immediately.
    Upon termination you must stop using the Software and destroy all
    copies in your possession.

END OF TERMS
